COLOMBO , September 13 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- The Sri Lankan Defense Ministry said Monday that the government 's latest offensive against the Tamil Tiger rebels have left 169 killed on both sides and hundreds wounded in the north of the country .
The ministry said government troops killed 116 rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam -LRB- LTTE -RRB- in the offensive launched on Sunday in the Mannar district , about 300 kilometers north of Colombo .
It said a large number of rebels were wounded .
The offensive , codenamed `` Operation Battle Cry '' which was launched after a nine-week lull in the conflict , has also left 53 soldiers killed and 411 others injured , 92 of them in serious condition , the ministry said .
The casualties are expected to mount as the operation is continuing , the ministry said .
Earlier , military officials said more than 100 LTTE rebels and 49 soldiers were killed in battles .
The army said it has launched a series of operations this year and captured more than 1,500 square kilometers of rebel-held territory .
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a war against the Sri Lankan government for a Tamil homeland in the north and east of the country since 1983 .
More than 55,000 people have been killed in the conflicts .
